Class HtmlVeryRestrictedFlowElement<T extends com.k2.XMLBuilder.XMLElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.k2.XMLBuilder.XMLNode
      • com.k2.XMLBuilder.XMLElement
        • com.k2.Html5Builder.HtmlGlobalElement<T>
          • com.k2.Html5Builder.HtmlElement<T>
            • com.k2.Html5Builder.HtmlCommonPhrasingElement<T>
              • com.k2.Html5Builder.HtmlVeryRestrictedFlowElement<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The final class implementing the html element
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HtmlAddress

    public abstract class HtmlVeryRestrictedFlowElement<T extends com.k2.XMLBuilder.XMLElement>
extends HtmlCommonPhrasingElement<T>
    This abstract element defines a flow element that disallows header, footer, address elements, headings and section This class adds the methods to create the child elements appropriate to flow elements excluding header, footer, address, heading and section elements
    Author:
    simon
